<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Workshop Setup on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/</link><description>Recent content in Workshop Setup on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>AWS Setup</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/1-aws-setup/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/1-aws-setup/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="enable-the-red-hat-openshift-service-in-aws"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Enable the Red Hat OpenShift Service in AWS&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#enable-the-red-hat-openshift-service-in-aws" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To deploy OpenShift in your AWS account, we&amp;rsquo;ll need to first enable the
Red Hat OpenShift service using the &lt;a href="https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/rosa/home?region=us-east-1#/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;AWS console&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next, follow the instructions to connect your AWS account with your Red Hat account.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="provision-an-ec2-instance"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Provision an EC2 Instance&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#provision-an-ec2-instance" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s provision an EC2 instance that we&amp;rsquo;ll use to deploy the Red Hat cluster. This avoids
the limitations running the ROSA command-line interface on Mac OS.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OpenShift Prerequisites</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/2-openshift-prereqs/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/2-openshift-prereqs/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The steps below are required before deploying the OpenShift cluster in AWS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="create-a-red-hat-login"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Create a Red Hat Login&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#create-a-red-hat-login" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first thing we&amp;rsquo;ll need to do is create an account with Red Hat, which we can do by
filling out the form
&lt;a href="https://www.redhat.com/wapps/ugc/register.html?_flowId=register-flow&amp;amp;_flowExecutionKey=e1s1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;here&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="install-the-aws-cli"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Install the AWS CLI&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#install-the-aws-cli" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To install the AWS CLI on the EC2 instance provisioned previously, run the following commands:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy OpenShift Cluster in AWS</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/3-deploy-openshift-cluster/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/3-deploy-openshift-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="deploy-an-openshift-cluster"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Deploy an OpenShift Cluster&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#deploy-an-openshift-cluster" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;rsquo;ll use the ROSA CLI to deploy an OpenShift Cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, we&amp;rsquo;ll need to set a few environment variables:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: be sure to fill in the Subnet IDs and OIDC ID before running the EXPORT commands&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;CLUSTER_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;rosa-test
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;AWS_REGION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;us-east-2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;AWS_INSTANCE_TYPE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;g5.4xlarge
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;SUBNET_IDS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;comma separated list of subnet IDs from earlier rosa create network command&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;OIDC_ID&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;the oidc-provider id returned from the rosa create oidc-config command&amp;gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;OPERATOR_ROLES_PREFIX&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;rosa-test-a6x9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create operator roles for the OIDC configuration using the following command:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy the NVIDIA NIM Operator</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/4-deploy-nvidia-nim/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/4-deploy-nvidia-nim/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;NVIDIA GPU Operator&lt;/strong&gt; is a Kubernetes Operator that automates the deployment, configuration,
and management of all necessary NVIDIA software components to provision GPUs within a Kubernetes cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;NVIDIA NIM Operator&lt;/strong&gt; is used to deploy LLMs in Kubernetes environments, such
as the OpenShift cluster we created earlier in this workshop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This section of the workshop walks through the steps necessary to deploy both the
NVIDIA GPU and NIM operators in our OpenShift cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy an LLM</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/5-deploy-llm/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/5-deploy-llm/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this section, we&amp;rsquo;ll use the NVIDIA NIM Operator to deploy two Large Language Models
to our OpenShift Cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="create-a-namespace"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Create a Namespace&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#create-a-namespace" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;oc create namespace nim-service&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="add-secrets-with-ngc-api-key"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Add Secrets with NGC API Key&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#add-secrets-with-ngc-api-key" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add a Docker registry secret for downloading container images from NVIDIA NGC:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;oc create secret -n nim-service docker-registry ngc-secret &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --docker-server&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;nvcr.io &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --docker-username&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;$oauthtoken&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --docker-password&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$NGC_API_KEY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add a generic secret that model puller containers use to download the model from NVIDIA NGC:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Setup Users</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/6-setup-users/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/6-setup-users/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this section, we&amp;rsquo;ll create users for each workshop participant, with a namespace and resource
quota for each.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="create-user-namespaces-and-resource-quotas"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Create User Namespaces and Resource Quotas&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#create-user-namespaces-and-resource-quotas" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; user-setup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;./create-namespaces.sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="create-users"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Create Users&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#create-users" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create an HTPasswd file with participant credentials, then replace
the ROSA-managed HTPasswd IdP with a custom one:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;./create-users.sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="re-create-the-cluster-admin-user-then-login-again"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Re-create the cluster-admin user then login again&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#re-create-the-cluster-admin-user-then-login-again" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re-create the cluster-admin user then login again:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Install the OpenTelemetry Collector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/7-install-otel-collector/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/7-install-otel-collector/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this section, we&amp;rsquo;ll install the OpenTelemetry collector with only the clusterReceiver enabled
(as the workshop participants will install their own agent in their namespace).
We&amp;rsquo;ll then take the ClusterRole created by this collector installation and bind it to
each of the workshop participant namespaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="install-the-opentelemetry-collector"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Install the OpenTelemetry Collector&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#install-the-opentelemetry-collector" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, we&amp;rsquo;ll create a new project for the collector and switch to that project:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;oc new-project admin-otel &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add the Splunk OpenTelemetry Collector for Kubernetes&amp;rsquo; Helm chart repository:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy the Vector Database</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/8-deploy-vector-db/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/8-deploy-vector-db/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this step, we&amp;rsquo;ll deploy a vector database to the OpenShift cluster and populate it with
test data that will be used by workshop participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="deploy-a-vector-database"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Deploy a Vector Database&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#deploy-a-vector-database" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the workshop, we&amp;rsquo;ll deploy an open-source vector database named
&lt;a href="https://weaviate.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Weaviate&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, add the Weaviate helm repo that contains the Weaviate helm chart:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;helm repo add weaviate https://weaviate.github.io/weaviate-helm
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;helm repo update&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;weaviate/weaviate-values.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file includes the configuration we&amp;rsquo;ll use to deploy
the Weviate vector database.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy the Portworx Metrics Endpoint</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/9-deploy-portworx-service/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/9-deploy-portworx-service/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this step, we&amp;rsquo;ll deploy a Python service that mimics the Portworx metrics endpoint.
This will be used in the workshop to configure monitoring for Pure Storage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="deploy-the-portworx-metrics-endpoint"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Deploy the Portworx Metrics Endpoint&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#deploy-the-portworx-metrics-endpoint" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to deploy the Portworx metrics endpoint service:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;oc new-project portworx
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;oc apply -f ./portworx/k8s.yaml -n portworx&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="test-the-portworx-metrics-endpoint"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Test the Portworx Metrics Endpoint&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#test-the-portworx-metrics-endpoint" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s ensure the Portworx metrics endpoint is working as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Clean Up</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/10-cleanup/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/infrastructure/14-cisco-ai-pods/1-workshop-setup/10-cleanup/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="clean-up-steps"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Clean Up Steps&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#clean-up-steps" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once the workshop is complete, follow the steps in this section to uninstall the OpenShift cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Get the cluster ID, the Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) for the cluster-specific Operator roles,
and the endpoint URL for the OIDC provider by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
